Clinical use of sildenafil in pulmonary artery hypertension.

Singh TP(1).

Author information:
(1)Prime Heart and Vascular Institute, Shivalik Hospital, Sector-69, Mohali, 
Punjab, India. tpsinghtp@yahoo.co.in

Severe pulmonary hypertension is a debilitating disease with short life 
expectancy that often affects young people. It is usually idiopathic pulmonary 
artery hypertension and is characterized by progressive elevation of pulmonary 
artery pressure and vascular resistance, right ventricular failure and death 
with a limited median survival time. There is an imbalance in vasoconstrictive 
