pulmonary and penile vasodilator initially approved for erectile dysfunction, is 
found to be efficacious in severe pulmonary artery hypertension. There are 
limited treatment options for the management of pulmonary artery hypertension in 
developing countries and sildenafil is a reasonable treatment option. This 
article reviews the relevant clinical data in pulmonary hypertension and the 
role of sildenafil in its management.

